# Core Security

## Secrets

- **Never** hardcode API keys, tokens, master passwords, or Zotero credentials in source.
- **Never** store BYOK secrets in `.env`. Only `VITE_*` compile-time flags per `@.env.example`.
- Cloud provider keys belong in the encrypted vault (`@src/lib/crypto.ts`, `@src/contexts/SecureConfigContext.tsx`).
- Use `.env` locally; commit only `.env.example`.

<example>
// Read debug flag only
const debug = import.meta.env.VITE_ENABLE_DEBUG_TOOLS === 'true';
</example>

<example type="invalid">
const GEMINI_KEY = 'sk-live-abc123'; // hardcoded in source
</example>

## PDF Ingestion

- Parse PDFs via `pdfjs-dist` text extraction only; never execute embedded PDF scripts.
- Treat uploaded PDF content as untrusted input in RAG chunking.

## External API Responses

- Validate and sanitize JSON from Zotero, Mendeley, PubMed, arXiv before rendering or persisting.
- Never inject API response strings via `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`.

## Error Handling & Logging

- Surface user-facing errors via `sonner` toasts and `@src/components/ErrorBoundary.tsx`.
- Log errors without secrets: redact keys, IVs, salts, and vault payloads.
- Prefer typed errors over silent `catch {}` blocks in security-sensitive paths.

<example>
console.error('Vault unlock failed', { provider: name });
</example>

<example type="invalid">
console.log('decrypted key', apiKey);
</example>

## CSP & Network

- Respect existing CSP constraints; new external endpoints require security review.
- Document new third-party origins in `@SECURITY.md` when adding fetch targets.
